 system. Don't sugar coat with easy exams and lets start comparing usa schools with schools of europe, china and Korea. See how we compare there. We are not even on the map..The greatest country in the world spending the most per child and 50% cant read or write at a decent level. But there are broken homes and much more to write about and this space isn't enough. Unfortunately for so many children that want to learn and deserve to learn there aren't many solutions if they don't have the economics of private school.  Lets hope we can squeeze unions and government out and we dont need to empty the private schools to do that. The ball after all is round and the game is only 90 minutes - lets not sacrifice generations to fix a union-politico problem. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1065" language="en" documentId="4202" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="LouizaP" date="Aug 29, 2013 5:38PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="9" thumbsDown="0" origId="4202" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1065"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>